When restoring a backup file, rather than a text field I think we should present the user with a list of the files in the restore directory (along with their file sizes, mod date, mod user etc). It's a much nicer UI, and there aren't really any security holes opened as they need to have access to the directory to put the file there in the first place - hence could just 'ls'!

